ment from a customer, purchases (or sells) the financial instrument for its own account to offset a contemporaneous sale to (or purchase from) the customer. (d) Permitted trading by a regulated insurance company.  The prohibition contained in § __.3(a) does not apply to the purchase or sale of financial instruments by a banking entity that is an insurance company or an affiliate of an insurance company if: (1) The insurance company or its affiliate purchases or sells the financial instruments solely for: (i)  The general account of the insurance company; or  (ii)  A separate account established by the insurance company; 
